DIAPHRAGM ENGINE

diaphragm_engine is the muscle citizen who breathes for fadriel
the diaphragm is a domed muscle separating the thoracic and abdominal cavities; when it contracts it flattens, increasing thoracic volume and drawing air into the lungs
the diaphragm runs continuously throughout fadriel's life, more constantly than any other voluntary muscle, including the postural ones
fadriel can voluntarily control breathing for short periods, but the brainstem maintains the rhythm during the vast majority of his life

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe muscle.zc
observe contract.rana
observe fiber_mix.rana
observe lungs.rana
observe ribcage.xb

the 7 properties of diaphragm_engine:
1 ENERGY zero point eight: continuously cycling
2 PHASE advances continuously through the breath cycle
3 SPIN one half during inspiration, minus zero point five during exhalation
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING one with lungs and ribcage

VERB inspire
contract, flattening the dome, drawing air in
the work is concentric and rhythmic

VERB expire
relax, allowing the dome to rise; air leaves the lungs by elastic recoil
expiration is mostly passive in fadriel; only forced exhalation engages the diaphragm actively

VERB pace_with_brainstem
take pacing signals from the respiratory centers in the medulla
fadriel can override briefly (holding breath, sighing, blowing out candles), but the brainstem reasserts rhythm

a breathing engine is the body's most reliable muscle
fadriel's diaphragm has not stopped since his first breath and will not stop until his last
its calcified rhythm is the substrate's commitment to keeping him alive without his attention
